//
// Per RFC-018 §10 + SPEC.yaml `linker.formats: [ELF, Mach-O_arm64]`:
// hexa_ld is the primary linker; system `ld` is the fallback. v1 shipped
// ELF only; v1.1 added a minimal Mach-O (arm64-apple-darwin) emitter.
// v1.2 (2026-05-10) adds embedded ad-hoc code signing so the kernel on
// Apple Silicon actually accepts the binary (without it XNU SIGKILLs the
// process before LC_MAIN — see Mach-O CAVEATS below).
//
// IN SCOPE (v1, ELF):
//   * Reads ONE ELF64 little-endian relocatable object (.o)
//   * Concatenates the .text section
//   * Resolves a single entry symbol (`_start`, falling back to `main`)
//   * Emits a STATIC ELF64 executable with one PT_LOAD (R+X, vaddr 0x400000).
//
// IN SCOPE (v1.1, Mach-O):
//   * Reads ONE Mach-O 64-bit relocatable object (MH_OBJECT, arm64).
//   * Locates the `__TEXT,__text` section bytes via LC_SEGMENT_64.
//   * Resolves entry symbol via LC_SYMTAB:
//       - `_main` first (Apple/clang default emits underscore)
//       - `start` fallback (matches `crt1.o` symbol on macOS)
//   * Emits an MH_EXECUTE Mach-O 64 binary with:
//       - mach_header_64 (cputype=ARM64=0x0100000C, cpusubtype=ALL=0)
//       - LC_SEGMENT_64 __PAGEZERO (vmaddr=0, vmsize=0x100000000, no file)
//       - LC_SEGMENT_64 __TEXT (vmaddr=0x100000000, R+X, contains __text)
//       - LC_LOAD_DYLINKER `/usr/lib/dyld`  (modern XNU rejects binaries
//         that lack it; needed even for "static" hello-world)
//       - LC_MAIN (cmd=0x80000028) with entryoff = (text_off + sym_off).
//   * Top-level `link()` autodetects the magic and dispatches.
//
// MACH-O CAVEATS (v1.1 → v1.2 update):
//   * Apple Silicon REQUIRES a valid code signature. v1.2 emits an
//     embedded ad-hoc LC_CODE_SIGNATURE blob (CSMAGIC_EMBEDDED_SIGNATURE
//     wrapping a CSMAGIC_CODEDIRECTORY with per-4 KiB-page SHA-256
//     hashes); the kernel CDHash check then succeeds without any
//     post-link `codesign -s -` shellout.
//   * Truly-static Mach-O (no LC_LOAD_DYLINKER) is NOT supported by
//     modern dyld/XNU on arm64 except for a small set of system bootstrap
//     binaries. We therefore include LC_LOAD_DYLINKER `/usr/lib/dyld`
//     and rely on the "no LC_LOAD_DYLIB" property to keep the program
//     dependency-free at runtime.
//   * No relocations applied: __text bytes that reference __got, __stubs,
//     or external symbols WILL crash. Use --linker=system for anything
//     beyond a hand-written entrypoint that returns immediately.
//   * v1.2 adds a minimal __LINKEDIT segment (covers the codesign blob
//     only — no symtab, no DYSYMTAB, no FUNCTION_STARTS yet). `dsymutil`,
//     `nm`, `dwarfdump` will still see an empty binary. Sufficient for
//     LC_CODE_SIGNATURE acceptance + smoke testing.
//
